Redis(R) can be accessed via port 6379 on the following DNS name from within your cluster:

    redis-master.streaming.svc.cluster.local

To get your password run:

    export REDIS_PASSWORD=$(kubectl get secret --namespace streaming redis -o jsonpath="{.data.redis-password}" | base64 -d)

To connect to your Redis(R) server:

1. Run a Redis(R) pod that you can use as a client:

   kubectl run --namespace streaming redis-client --restart='Never'  --env REDIS_PASSWORD=$REDIS_PASSWORD  --image registry-1.docker.io/bitnami/redis:latest --command -- sleep infinity

   Use the following command to attach to the pod:

   kubectl exec --tty -i redis-client \
   --namespace streaming -- bash

2. Connect using the Redis(R) CLI:
   REDISCLI_AUTH="$REDIS_PASSWORD" redis-cli -h redis-master

To connect to your database from outside the cluster execute the following commands:

    kubectl port-forward --namespace streaming svc/redis-master 6379:6379 &
    REDISCLI_AUTH="$REDIS_PASSWORD" redis-cli -h 127.0.0.1 -p 6379
